description:
BREAKING: Tom Aspinall becomes the undisputed UFC Heavyweight Champion. He reveals the truth about Jon Jones’ retirement, and breaks down the champion mindset, fear, and mental toughness required for UFC title fights. 

Tom explains: 
◽️The mental trick he uses to control fear before stepping into the cage.
◽️ Why so many young men feel lost, and how MMA gave him purpose.
◽️ The harsh reality of life as a UFC fighter behind the scenes.
◽️How embracing pain, pressure, and adversity made him a champion.

comments.text:
I think what makes Tom so inspirational and charismatic is this quite confidence he has. 

He is not dishonest, quite the opposite. He admits to being afraid. 

In retrospect it is quite interesting to see how many people fell for McGregor’s confidence during his reign. 

The difference to me and why I prefer tom is that what made McGregor attractive was that he was actually having fun for a while, but he was lying in terms of his confidence. There was always a hint of inauthenticity there (especially in hindsight). 

Tom has that confidence, but contrary to McGregor he does not mask his shortcomings, he admits to fear. McGregor would have simply denied any kind of fear. And in the end that was his downfall, because he made the “image” so enticing that he couldn’t let it go for himself, when he himself needed to move on and accept that his time was over.
